msgid ""
"If both of these parameters are set to true, :code:`struct folio` for this "
"capacity will be carved out of the memory block being onlined.  This has "
"performance implications if the memory is particularly high-latency and its :"
"code:`struct folio` becomes hotly contended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/linux/memory-hotplug.rst:62
msgid ""
"If either parameter is set to false, :code:`struct folio` for this capacity "
"will be allocated from the local node of the processor running the hotplug "
"procedure.  This capacity will be allocated from :code:`ZONE_NORMAL` on that "
"node, as it is a :code:`GFP_KERNEL` allocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/linux/memory-hotplug.rst:67
msgid ""
"Systems with extremely large amounts of :code:`ZONE_MOVABLE` memory (e.g. "
"CXL memory pools) must ensure that there is sufficient local :code:"
"`ZONE_NORMAL` capacity to host the memory map for the hotplugged capacity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/linux/memory-hotplug.rst:72
msgid "Driver Managed Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/linux/memory-hotplug.rst:73
msgid ""
"The DAX driver surfaces this memory to memory-hotplug as \"Driver Managed\". "
"This is not a configurable setting, but it's important to note that driver "
"managed memory is explicitly excluded from use during kexec.  This is "
"required to ensure any reset or out-of-band operations that the CXL device "
"may be subject to during a functional system-reboot (such as a reset-on-"
"probe) will not cause portions of the kexec kernel to be overwritten."
msgstr ""
